name: Isla Bell
summary: Human remains discovered during the search for missing Victorian woman Isla Bell have led to the arrest of two men. The 19-year-old was reported missing on December 17th from Pakenham in Melbourne's southeast. Detectives investigating her disappearance identified and charged two men, with one facing a murder charge. The deceased remains were found at a tip during the investigation, and authorities have confirmed their identity as Isla Bell. Her mother expressed her grief, stating that her daughter's memory would be cherished while acknowledging the end of her suffering. This grim discovery and subsequent charges bring closure to Isla Bell's loved ones while highlighting the ongoing efforts to find missing persons.

name: Dr Oz
summary: Former President Trump has selected Dr. Mehmet Oz, a television personality and cardiothoracic surgeon, to lead the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS), the agency that oversees Medicare and Medicaid. This nomination has raised concerns among healthcare professionals and advocates, who question Dr. Oz's qualifications and track record on healthcare issues. Critics have pointed to his history of promoting unproven medical claims and his lack of experience in managing large healthcare programs. The nomination has also been met with controversy due to Dr. Oz's previous support for former President Trump and his alleged involvement in the January 6, 2021, attack on the US Capitol. The nomination requires Senate confirmation, and it remains unclear whether Dr. Oz will be approved for the role.

name: Interior Chinatown
summary: "Interior Chinatown," a Hulu miniseries, has received mixed reviews from various publications. Roger Ebert praised Jimmy O. Yang's performance as he excels in the excellent "Interior Chinatown." The Guardian acknowledged the adaptation's ambition but found it tiring. Mashable considered it a highly ambitious and meta police procedural spoof. The Hollywood Reporter noted Jimmy O. Yang's growth but criticized the show's excessive meta-ness. Polygon listed it among new TV releases, while Town and Country TODAY highlighted the cast's relatable Hollywood experiences. The A.V. Club appreciated the campy and charming take on "Interior Chinatown." Screen Rant praised the series as a biting meta commentary on Asian-American representation. However, Variety expressed challenges in adapting the allegorical novel into a show, and Mashable emphasized the show's ability to highlight the invisibility of Asian Americans.

'Astro Bot' and 'Final Fantasy VII Rebirth' are the frontrunners with seven nominations each, while other nominees include 'God of War Ragnarok', 'Elden Ring', and 'Stray'. DLCs, remakes, remasters, and expansions are now eligible for Game of the Year and other awards, a change from previous years that has sparked controversy. The full list of nominees can be found on the Game Awards website. The ceremony will take place on December 8th, 2024, and will be streamed live on various platforms including YouTube, Twitch, and Facebook.

name: St Kilda
summary: The St. Kilda Football Club, a prominent team in the Australian Football League (AFL), has officially unveiled a revamped logo that marks the beginning of a "new era" for the club. The modernized crest is designed to reflect the Saints' bold and progressive approach. In other news, the team is considering an innovative strategy in the upcoming AFL Draft, as they aim to bolster their roster with talented players from a deep pool. The club's revised logo, which symbolizes strength and power, is part of an overall image reset ahead of the 2025 AFL season. Additionally, St. Kilda is contemplating signing a player from the SANFL to support their star ruckman, Rowan Marshall. Finally, the team's 2025 fixture has been released, featuring back-to-back Friday night matches and a return to the iconic Melbourne Cricket Ground (MCG).
